cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the generalization of a convolutional neural network trained to identify cars using different image datasets obtained from cameras and ray-traced multispectral synthetic images. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of camera parameters on CNN generalization, which is a common topic in the computer vision field. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses a neural network for image classification. The experiments conducted in the paper to simulate sensor images with different pixel sizes, color filters, acquisition, and post-acquisition processing involve machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with image datasets obtained from cameras and ray-traced multispectral synthetic images. Finally, the paper involves graphics (cs.GR) as it uses ISETAuto, a soft prototyping tool that creates ray-traced multispectral simulations of camera images.
